HEADWORD: Lobule
<hw>Lob"ule</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>lobule</ets>, dim. of
<ets>lobe</ets>. See <er>Lobe</er>.]</ety> <def>A small lobe; a
subdivision of a lobe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Lobule of the ear</b></col>. <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <cd>Same
as <cref>Lobe of the ear</cref>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lobulette</ent>⟦br⟧
